Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Greek Prime Minister Alexis Tsipras to express appreciation for his leadership and that of Macedonian Prime Minister Zoran Zaev on efforts to resolve the name dispute. They agreed that there is an opportunity to resolve the issue and that time is crucial. The Vice President encouraged Prime Minister Tsipras to continue working with Prime Minister Zaev on reaching an agreement. Resolving the issue would promote stability and peace in the region.